No lassa there either.

260
00:11:16,317 --> 00:11:17,551
Oh.

261
00:11:17,618 --> 00:11:18,584
Again.

262
00:11:18,650 --> 00:11:20,017
Trypanosomiasis?

263
00:11:20,084 --> 00:11:22,184
No sleep disturbances.

264
00:11:22,251 --> 00:11:23,417
But fits best
with the symptoms.

265
00:11:23,484 --> 00:11:24,518
And it's geographically
the most--

266
00:11:24,584 --> 00:11:25,551
What?

267
00:11:25,618 --> 00:11:26,984
The egypt visit

268
00:11:27,050 --> 00:11:28,484
Was for the african union
meeting,

269
00:11:28,551 --> 00:11:30,017
Where i'm guessing he was
meeting people

270
00:11:30,084 --> 00:11:31,217
From africa.

271
00:11:31,284 --> 00:11:33,317
Which includes liberia,

272
00:11:33,384 --> 00:11:34,683
Which sent some members
of their foreign ministry,

273
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:35,750
Which has itself
just been hit by an outbreak

274
00:11:35,817 --> 00:11:37,817
Of jock itch.

275
00:11:37,884 --> 00:11:40,084
No, wait.
not jock itch.

276
00:11:40,151 --> 00:11:41,217
Lassa fever.

277
00:11:43,417 --> 00:11:45,117
I'll start the ribavirin.

278
00:11:46,584 --> 00:11:48,084
I did say it up front.

279
00:11:48,151 --> 00:11:52,484
It's great to have the old team
back together again, huh?

280
00:11:56,650 --> 00:11:57,650
<i>(ntila)
yesterday,</i>

281
00:11:57,717 --> 00:11:59,650
It's poisoning.
today, lassa fever.

282
00:11:59,717 --> 00:12:01,251
<i>maybe a specialist--</i>

283
00:12:01,317 --> 00:12:02,084
<i>(dibala)
joseph!</i>

284
00:12:02,151 --> 00:12:05,251
Leave him alone.

285
00:12:05,317 --> 00:12:09,484
These people know
what they are doing.

286
00:12:09,551 --> 00:12:10,917
Are you married,
doctor?

287
00:12:10,984 --> 00:12:12,551
No.

288
00:12:12,618 --> 00:12:15,284
<i>you have a girlfriend.</i>

289
00:12:15,351 --> 00:12:16,484
Yes.

290
00:12:16,551 --> 00:12:19,584
Judging
by your tentative answer

291
00:12:19,650 --> 00:12:22,850
And the complicated expression
on her face,

292
00:12:22,917 --> 00:12:26,717
I believe that is she,
standing in the hallway.

293
00:12:32,451 --> 00:12:33,783
I got a call
from douglas' department

294
00:12:33,850 --> 00:12:35,451
At princeton general.

295
00:12:35,518 --> 00:12:37,618
They want me
to interview with them.

296
00:12:37,683 --> 00:12:38,950
Which is weird,
because when i called

297
00:12:39,017 --> 00:12:40,817
Last week, they said
they had nothing available.

298
00:12:40,884 --> 00:12:42,650
So i never sent in my resume.

299
00:12:42,717 --> 00:12:44,984
Douglas owes me a favor.

300
00:12:45,050 --> 00:12:46,750
Most people send chocolates.

301
00:12:46,817 --> 00:12:48,917
I'd stand outside your apartment
all night

302
00:12:48,984 --> 00:12:50,184
Holding up a boom box,
except you told me

303
00:12:50,251 --> 00:12:52,251
You hate '80s music.

304
00:13:00,151 --> 00:13:02,950
I'm free tomorrow night.

305
00:13:07,251 --> 00:13:09,618
[keys jangle]

306
00:13:25,184 --> 00:13:27,584
I was wondering
what that noise was.

307
00:13:27,650 --> 00:13:28,950
It's the damn cane.

308
00:13:29,017 --> 00:13:30,484
And i'm greg.

309
00:13:30,551 --> 00:13:31,717
And i can't sleep

310
00:13:31,783 --> 00:13:34,683
With you banging around
with that thing.

311
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:36,151
You're not actually saying

312
00:13:36,217 --> 00:13:37,683
That i have too loud
a cane?

313
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:40,783
Is that hard
for you to understand?

314
00:13:40,850 --> 00:13:42,683
Only in the sense that it has
a rubber tip on the end

315
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:44,084
And not a tap shoe.

316
00:13:44,151 --> 00:13:45,984
Now you're getting cute
with me.

317
00:13:46,050 --> 00:13:49,184
Okay, we started badly.

318
00:13:49,251 --> 00:13:51,683
I apologize
for the noise,

319
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:53,817
And we will try to figure out
a way to be quieter--

320
00:13:53,884 --> 00:13:56,251
And a thousand other things
i don't give a crap about.

321
00:13:56,317 --> 00:13:57,917
Now you keep it down,

322
00:13:57,984 --> 00:13:59,650
Or we're gonna have trouble.

323
00:14:05,050 --> 00:14:07,050
Wow.
[door slams]

324
00:14:10,683 --> 00:14:11,984
<i>(cameron)
you paged me?</i>

325
00:14:12,050 --> 00:14:13,384
This is ama.

326
00:14:15,618 --> 00:14:17,518
<i>she is from our country,
but she lives here now.</i>

327
00:14:17,584 --> 00:14:19,518
We'd like you
to use her blood.

328
00:14:19,584 --> 00:14:21,518
For what?

329
00:14:21,584 --> 00:14:22,950
She recovered
from lassa fever

330
00:14:23,017 --> 00:14:23,984
Two years ago.

331
00:14:24,050 --> 00:14:26,184
<i>our health minister</i>

332
00:14:26,251 --> 00:14:28,618
<i>has advised us that plasma</i>

333
00:14:28,683 --> 00:14:30,217
<i>from one who has
the antibodies</i>

334
00:14:30,284 --> 00:14:31,850
Is much more effective

335
00:14:31,917 --> 00:14:32,917
Than ribavirin.

336
00:14:32,984 --> 00:14:34,417
This is a signed consent form.

337
00:14:34,484 --> 00:14:37,683
Will you take her blood, please?

338
00:14:41,050 --> 00:14:42,717
No.

339
00:14:42,783 --> 00:14:44,683
I want to do this.

340
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:46,117
<i>(cuddy)
you understand
that we would be using</i>

341
00:14:46,184 --> 00:14:48,884
Your blood
to cure president dibala.

342
00:14:48,950 --> 00:14:50,351
I know.

343
00:14:50,417 --> 00:14:52,117
Are you
from the sitibi people?

344
00:14:52,184 --> 00:14:53,683
I am sitibi.

345
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:55,683
Did they threaten you
in some way?

346
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:56,717
<i>your family members
back home?</i>

347
00:14:56,783 --> 00:14:58,584
Please let me
give the blood.

348
00:14:58,650 --> 00:14:59,518
Please.

349
00:15:01,717 --> 00:15:03,050
Do it.

350
00:15:03,117 --> 00:15:05,317
She's being coerced.

351
00:15:05,384 --> 00:15:08,683
If she is, i'd rather have
a needle prick

352
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:11,251
On my conscience than the death
of her family members.

353
00:15:38,117 --> 00:15:39,817
Hey!

354
00:15:39,884 --> 00:15:41,984
Don't let him in there!

355
00:15:42,050 --> 00:15:44,284
[gunshots]

356
00:15:44,351 --> 00:15:46,251
[beating
and gasping]

357
00:15:50,817 --> 00:15:52,451
<i>(bass)
hey!</i>

358
00:15:52,518 --> 00:15:53,750
That's enough!
we got him.

359
00:15:53,817 --> 00:15:54,650
Hey!

360
00:15:56,783 --> 00:15:59,017
[shouts]
you all right?

361
00:15:59,084 --> 00:16:00,618
Who is that man?

362
00:16:07,619 --> 00:16:08,619
He shot him?

363
00:16:09,620 --> 00:16:10,620
No.

364
00:16:16,017 --> 00:16:16,918
<i>(chase)
you need a lawyer.</i>

365
00:16:16,983 --> 00:16:19,651
You can get
a court-appointed.

366
00:16:19,717 --> 00:16:20,851
They can help you.

367
00:16:20,918 --> 00:16:23,284
I can't be helped.

368
00:16:23,350 --> 00:16:27,184
You did a stupid,
terrible thing.

369
00:16:27,250 --> 00:16:29,217
But given the circumstances
with your wife,

370
00:16:29,284 --> 00:16:34,417
You could get
a reduced sentence.

371
00:16:34,484 --> 00:16:37,083
She wasn't my wife.

372
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:40,317
Then who was she?

373
00:16:40,384 --> 00:16:43,950
They never told us
her name.

374
00:16:48,117 --> 00:16:51,484
What his men made us do

375
00:16:51,551 --> 00:16:54,818
To that woman...

376
00:16:54,884 --> 00:16:57,017
He is now going to do

377
00:16:57,083 --> 00:17:01,717
To all the sitibi.

378
00:17:03,918 --> 00:17:04,784
(cameron)
you could have gotten killed.

379
00:17:04,851 --> 00:17:06,284
He wasn't going
to hurt me.

380
00:17:06,350 --> 00:17:08,150
He fired a gun
in the hospital.

381
00:17:10,217 --> 00:17:12,017
Come here.

382
00:17:17,617 --> 00:17:19,484
Maybe next time
don't yell out that warning.

383
00:17:24,717 --> 00:17:26,551
The bloody eye was
from an enlarged lymph node

384
00:17:26,617 --> 00:17:27,717
Blocking the retinal vein.

385
00:17:27,784 --> 00:17:29,584
We restored circulation,

386
00:17:29,651 --> 00:17:30,818
But it means we've got
to add lymph involvement

387
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:33,684
To the heart, lungs,
and rising fever.

388
00:17:33,751 --> 00:17:36,851
I'm just gonna sit here
quietly.

389
00:17:36,918 --> 00:17:39,050
Why?

390
00:17:39,117 --> 00:17:40,918
I feel like i've been
inadvertently undermining

391
00:17:40,983 --> 00:17:43,651
Your authority,
so i'm just gonna observe.

392
00:17:43,717 --> 00:17:46,983
Not gonna say a word.

393
00:17:47,050 --> 00:17:49,384
The heart could point
to sarcoidosis.

394
00:17:49,451 --> 00:17:50,317
[clears throat loudly]

395
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:58,617
I'm thinking
the x-rays indicate

396
00:17:58,684 --> 00:18:01,217
A lack of hilar adenopathy,

397
00:18:01,284 --> 00:18:02,217
Which rules it out.

398
00:18:04,284 --> 00:18:05,317
Staph aureus?

399
00:18:07,184 --> 00:18:08,651
<i>(chase)
no.</i>

400
00:18:08,717 --> 00:18:12,751
Because...

401
00:18:12,818 --> 00:18:14,217
He...

402
00:18:14,284 --> 00:18:17,150
Smokes?

403
00:18:17,217 --> 00:18:18,851
He's miming a thermometer.

404
00:18:18,918 --> 00:18:21,050
He says the fever's
not high enough.

405
00:18:21,117 --> 00:18:23,751
So some other infection.

406
00:18:23,818 --> 00:18:24,617
<i>(foreman)
he's wrong.</i>

407
00:18:24,684 --> 00:18:25,751
The fever could be misleading us

408
00:18:25,818 --> 00:18:28,451
Into thinking infection.

409
00:18:28,517 --> 00:18:29,884
Talk.

410
00:18:34,417 --> 00:18:35,983
It could all fit
with lymphoma.

411
00:18:42,350 --> 00:18:45,250
Um, i need you to spread
your legs so i can do an h.

412
00:18:45,317 --> 00:18:47,684
Can't be lymphoma.

413
00:18:47,751 --> 00:18:50,184
Ldh is normal.

414
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:51,950
He's got good liver function.

415
00:18:52,017 --> 00:18:53,950
It's masking
the elevated levels.

416
00:18:54,017 --> 00:18:58,451
Biopsy the lymph node.
check it out.

417
00:18:58,517 --> 00:19:00,117
Makes sense.

418
00:19:00,184 --> 00:19:02,918
I guess you don't need me.

419
00:19:04,784 --> 00:19:06,317
Oh, by the way,

420
00:19:06,384 --> 00:19:08,083
You might want
to close the blinds.

421
00:19:08,150 --> 00:19:10,250
A little bright in here.

422
00:19:19,050 --> 00:19:21,017
It's just a wild coincidence
that he thought

423
00:19:21,083 --> 00:19:22,184
You were a rude jerk.

424
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:23,884
Come on. give me
the benefit of the doubt.

425
00:19:23,950 --> 00:19:25,551
You said he's a jerk.
i barely talked.

426
00:19:25,617 --> 00:19:26,983
You talked!

427
00:19:29,584 --> 00:19:32,551
All i wanted was to sip
morning espresso

428
00:19:32,617 --> 00:19:34,150
Next to a peaceful,
burbling fountain.

429
00:19:34,217 --> 00:19:37,451
You could be sipping courvoisier

430
00:19:37,517 --> 00:19:39,150
Next to a replica
of the playboy grotto

431
00:19:39,217 --> 00:19:41,184
If you tell him
what you got on him.

432
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:42,651
I don't have anything
on him.

433
00:19:42,717 --> 00:19:44,050
I don't want anything
on him.

434
00:19:44,117 --> 00:19:46,250
The closest he's been
to vietnam?

435
00:19:46,317 --> 00:19:49,784
Ordering the mee krob
at that place on the corner.

436
00:19:49,851 --> 00:19:51,350
Mee krob
is from thailand.

437
00:19:51,417 --> 00:19:52,717
Exactly.

438
00:19:52,784 --> 00:19:53,751
What did you do?

439
00:19:53,818 --> 00:19:55,184
Why do you think he's faking?

440
00:19:55,250 --> 00:19:57,050
I saw his mail.
your broke in?

441
00:19:57,117 --> 00:19:58,950
No.
he was holding it.

442
00:19:59,017 --> 00:20:00,551
<i>private medical insurance.</i>

443
00:20:00,617 --> 00:20:03,184
Not from the v.a.

444
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:05,584
Plus, he's got
to be early 50s.

445
00:20:05,651 --> 00:20:06,684
He's too young
to be a vet.

446
00:20:06,751 --> 00:20:07,784
So i looked further.

447
00:20:07,851 --> 00:20:08,751
You did break in.

448
00:20:08,818 --> 00:20:10,717
Online.

449
00:20:10,784 --> 00:20:12,784
There's no reference to him
in any of the vet records.

450
00:20:12,851 --> 00:20:14,751
Why would he fake
being a veteran?

451
00:20:14,818 --> 00:20:16,717
Just look
how you're acting.

452
00:20:16,784 --> 00:20:19,751
People have been tiptoeing
around this jerk for years.

453
00:20:19,818 --> 00:20:23,050
Normally, we'd all tell
the amputee to go screw himself.

454
00:20:23,117 --> 00:20:24,584
Victims get pity,
heroes get adulation.

455
00:20:24,651 --> 00:20:25,684
It's way better.

456
00:20:25,751 --> 00:20:26,950
Thank you for trying
to help me out

457
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:27,950
With my neighbor.

458
00:20:28,017 --> 00:20:28,918
Now forget the vietnam stuff.

459
00:20:28,983 --> 00:20:30,651
I could prove this.

460
00:20:30,717 --> 00:20:32,417
But you won't
because you'll be too busy

461
00:20:32,484 --> 00:20:33,751
Writing him a letter
of apology

462
00:20:33,818 --> 00:20:35,451
And dropping it
at his door

463
00:20:35,517 --> 00:20:38,217
Without knocking
at his door.

464
00:20:38,284 --> 00:20:39,350
I dil ass.

465
00:20:39,417 --> 00:20:40,551
Which is the point.

466
00:20:40,617 --> 00:20:43,250
It's easy to be nice
to people you like.

467
00:20:43,317 --> 00:20:44,918
But being nice
to people you hate,

468
00:20:44,983 --> 00:20:46,117
That's a skill.

469
00:20:46,184 --> 00:20:47,983
Do it.

470
00:20:52,284 --> 00:20:54,350
Thank you
for saving my life.

471
00:20:54,417 --> 00:20:57,184
The man
that tried to kill you,

472
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:59,384
<i>he said that you were
preparing a massacre.</i>

473
00:21:03,083 --> 00:21:06,384
The sitibi are my countrymen.

474
00:21:06,451 --> 00:21:10,517
I am fighting
a guerilla war.

475
00:21:10,584 --> 00:21:12,983
In a way that's
being called genocide.

476
00:21:13,050 --> 00:21:15,651
20 years ago,

477
00:21:15,717 --> 00:21:18,918
These same sitibi rebels
took over the south,

478
00:21:18,983 --> 00:21:21,983
They massacred
tens of thousands,

479
00:21:22,050 --> 00:21:24,117
And they would happily do it
again.

480
00:21:24,184 --> 00:21:27,217
I'm trying
to impose order.

481
00:21:27,284 --> 00:21:30,751
I'm trying to prevent
a genocide.

482
00:21:30,818 --> 00:21:32,017
Genocide.

483
00:21:32,083 --> 00:21:35,384
<i>my own son,</i>

484
00:21:35,451 --> 00:21:36,651
My youngest,

485
00:21:36,717 --> 00:21:38,684
He is a student here.

486
00:21:38,751 --> 00:21:40,918
He hasn't spoken
to me in years

487
00:21:40,983 --> 00:21:44,250
Because of what he read
in your newspapers.

488
00:21:44,317 --> 00:21:46,484
But what he read
is not true.

489
00:21:46,551 --> 00:21:48,451
What about
your youth labor league?

490
00:21:51,117 --> 00:21:54,350
[sighs]

491
00:21:54,417 --> 00:21:59,983
There i was at fault.

492
00:22:00,050 --> 00:22:02,451
I hired men, who,
in their zeal,

493
00:22:02,517 --> 00:22:05,384
Stepped over the line,

494
00:22:05,451 --> 00:22:07,983
And there were abuses.

495
00:22:08,050 --> 00:22:13,784
But that will not happen again.

496
00:22:58,818 --> 00:23:01,117
Hello?

497
00:23:33,017 --> 00:23:34,417
How's it going?

498
00:23:34,484 --> 00:23:36,184
Normal-looking nucleus.

499
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:37,818
How's it going
with you?

500
00:23:37,884 --> 00:23:39,484
<i>it worried me
when you joked</i>

501
00:23:39,551 --> 00:23:40,918
About letting
that man shoot dibala.

502
00:23:40,983 --> 00:23:43,784
I wasn't joking.

503
00:23:43,851 --> 00:23:45,417
You can't want
to kill anyone,

504
00:23:45,484 --> 00:23:46,851
Especially not
your own patient.

505
00:23:46,918 --> 00:23:48,818
It's only natural
to feel he should--

506
00:23:48,884 --> 00:23:50,417
No, it's completely unnatural.

507
00:23:50,484 --> 00:23:52,417
Only psychopaths can kill
other people

508
00:23:52,484 --> 00:23:53,717
<i>without having some sort
of breakdown.</i>

509
00:23:53,784 --> 00:23:55,083
Not when it's justified.
look at soldiers.

510
00:23:55,150 --> 00:23:56,818
Even when it's justified.

511
00:23:56,884 --> 00:23:58,884
Am i trying
to kill our patient?

512
00:23:58,950 --> 00:24:00,384
Of course not.

513
00:24:00,451 --> 00:24:02,250
But if he died, am i supposed
to just pretend

514
00:24:02,317 --> 00:24:03,451
That wouldn't be good
for the world?

515
00:24:05,451 --> 00:24:06,983
The cells
are neatly differentiated.

516
00:24:07,050 --> 00:24:10,050
This isn't lymphoma.

517
00:24:12,150 --> 00:24:13,517
<i>(house)
thought i had detected</i>

518
00:24:13,584 --> 00:24:16,083
The sickly sweet smell
of maple syrup

519
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:18,284
And socialized medicine.

520
00:24:18,350 --> 00:24:20,884
It smells like...

521
00:24:20,950 --> 00:24:23,150
Victory.

522
00:24:23,217 --> 00:24:24,584
That big flag
in your place

523
00:24:24,651 --> 00:24:27,317
Prompted me to chat
with your housekeeper.

524
00:24:27,384 --> 00:24:29,417
Turns out you're a citizen
of the great white north.

525
